The paper deals with data dissemination in wireless networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The use of game theory in the proposed decentralized approach suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of game theory (cs.GT). The social cost minimization problem and the use of virtual tokens suggest that it could also belong to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The use of maximal-ratio combining and the consideration of power consumption suggest that it could also belong to the sub-category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) or information theory (cs.IT).
